name: Neighborhood Healthcare Riverside Latham
review_text:
The staff I interacted with were friendly enough and the facility seemed clean the short time I was there. I needed a new PCP for my child and selected one from this location via my insurer's website. Waited two weeks for his appointment which was today.  When we arrived and showed our insurance card I was told they do not accept our insurance even though one of their providers was listed on the card as my son's PCP. I wound up having to leave and called my insurer so they could update their information. I then found out that this medical office is actually  in  fact in network with my insurance and had been since October of 2023. My insurance agent offered to call the office and inform the staff for me, but I declined.
I'd say from the looks of things this is probably a decent medical office, but they're clearly confused on what insurers they are contracted with.

Love love love these doctors!
Dr. Hasrouni has been my primary care doctor and have nothing but positive experience with him! He takes the time to listen to all concerns and makes sure to answer all questions I have. I'm always recommending to friends and family of this doctor and facility.
This last appointment I had I took advantage of making an appt with the dental side as a new patient and needed a tooth extraction and let me tell you. Dr. Magarro was excellent! I was so nervous since it had been such time since I've seen a dentist snd let's be honest, who likes getting teeth pulled, but he took the time to make sure I was okay and made me laugh and smile to help me stay calm. Even his assistant was excellent!

Thank you to both doctors and assistants for amazing care and wonderful vibes! I will always recommend!

name: Neighborhood Healthcare Riverside Latham
review_text: No, this place isn't it. I tried it, and I'll never be back. The nurses and receptionist were very nice, but I felt like the PA Maria Lopez really didn't care about my issues. Just let me ramble and showed no interest or care for what I had to say. Seemed like my pains didn't matter, and my depression was a joke. I'm just going to take all of my issues over to Loma Linda, at least they actually try to be professional and helpful with me, I thought I'd try this place and it was a mistake. Just know that if you have depression or anxiety, no one here will help you. It's more like an urgent care if anything.
